reviews.review: I wonder if they knew it was this bad, it could have been worse and it was stuck by the previous movie but it sucked nonetheless. It is a good movie to pass time but as a Star Wars fun I feel like they destroyed the old 6 movies with this trilogy and this last one in particular.
People saying this movie is the worst, can go to hell. It's pathetic how they overanalyze a movie that's made to be fun and enjoyable! This one definitely was. Great movie!
Entertaining enough but destroys so much Star Wars lore.  It tries to make you feel things at every turn, but i felt....nothing.
Plot holes, galore. Like we are supposed to believe a whole fleet of ships no supply, encased in ice with crew just rose up after years. Ridiculous

Great movie.  It is impossible to please everyone. The people that were never going to like this movie will hate it regardless of anything.  Many people hate Rey (women can't be a strong action hero) and some hate the social message that was part of this new trilogy, they will never give this move a fair review.  I've watched all 9 movies in the theaters, played with the original figures and toys in the 1970s.  My children have seen all the movies.  My oldest (daughter) watched all the Clone Wars cartoons and played with all the toys growing up.  She loves Rey and Ahsoka Tano from Clone Wars.  They showed her that girls can be heroes too.  I was disappointed that the Force Awakens and Last Jedi let Luke end his part in this trilogy without the awesome lightsaber duels I always imagined him having when I was a kid growing up.  Rey pulls off some amazing force powered actions and lightsaber  action in this movie.  Hey guys, get over it she is a girl, still a good movie.

So I hated the Last Jedi, it really underwhelmed me and I had some reservations going into rise of Skywalker but I was pleasantly surprised, the movie was fun, funny and engaging, I was hooked on with what was going on, I teared up a few times. I laughed a bunch and I was on the edge of my seat, I think with the oof last Jedi did, rise of Skywalker tried its best to be a good ending and it definitely was

Great end to 9 movies, the best of the three, I’d love to see it in 3D next. I don’t want to spoil it but the end end was the best and don’t want around there is nothing after the credits unless you want to know who voiced the new droid.  Then you can leave.  5 star all around fun and action packed.

So on the whole I went in with low expectations in hopes they would be lifted by a good movie. What I got is not only that all the leaks from weeks leading up to this being true, but to over get 2 hours of pure chaos and no direction. Not only did they try tie everything in a neat little bow, but they did so in a way that not only retconned the original 3 movies but also the 2 before this one. You basically erased anything that was setup in TFA and TLJ for what? To introduce new characters and give no back story to how the emperor survives but was cloning snoke? SERIOUSLY Disney how could you even think this was a fitting end to this franchise? If you haven't seen this yet don't waste your money, wait till it comes out on disney +.... My soul is sad and angry that my childhood has been bastardized and ruined by greed and incompetence.

Ignore any negative reviews. This is a love letter from the bottom of the heart to the entire legacy and fan base of Star Wars. If you’ve ever been a fan of this world, just relax and let the feelings wash over you. We won’t have the chance to do this ever again.
You know it's bad when they can't even get the opening crawl right.
